terms.definition: A contract between a company and an individual who provides services as a non-employee.
At the present moment, often used in legal documents to signify an immediate action or statement.
Payments made by workers and employers to fund the Social Security program, which provides retirement, disability, and survivor benefits.
For that reason; consequently; used to introduce a conclusion based on what has just been stated.
Considering that; used to introduce background information or recitals in a legal document.
Insurance that provides income replacement if a person is unable to work due to illness or injury.
In this document, agreement, or matter.
In exchange for; as payment or compensation for.
Agreements and commitments made by two or more parties to each other.
Taxes that employers are required to withhold from employee paychecks or pay on behalf of their employees.
The main location where a company's business activities are conducted and where its executive officers direct operations.
The services that were previously mentioned or referred to in the document.
The accomplishment of a task or project to an acceptable standard or level.
Having complete and exclusive duty or blame for something.
Ended or brought to a conclusion.
Taxes paid by employers to fund benefits for workers who lose their jobs through no fault of their own.
A formal communication or announcement provided in written form.
